inlineContent.text: Minimum iOS version is: 13, the iOS SDK used for compiling is 16.0 (Xcode 14.2)
Here is a summary of various iOS specific systems and how they are supported.
Currently only portrait orientation is supported (with exception of the document scan module which is presented in landscape mode).
We have created step by step tutorial to make the integration easier -
. The previously available integration guide is deprecated in favor of the tutorials, may not include the latest information, and will be removed in the next releases.

abstract.text: IDCheckUILib is an UI layer on top of the IDCheckLib that simplifies it’s integration into your project.

This controller appears at the very beginning of the process, just after the document selection screen, if the preferred scan mode is .ask, when the user is asked to specify if the document has the chip
This view controller is used to allow user the selection of the EMRTD mode
This delegate protocol is the main way of communication between the IDCheckUI and the integrating code
This controller appears when the NFC is being read
This is the main view controller of the IDCheckUI, ideally you should place an instance of this class as your window.rootViewController
Step-by-step guide on how to integrate the IDCheckUILib into your app.

Defines which scan mode will be used when scanning the document. The .full mode scans the document, together with hologram etc. The .preNFC mode additionally reads the NFC chip of the document. The .ask mode will display a view to the user asking them if their document has the chip, and continue with the best scanning mode depending on the user choice.
